  "description": "Super Banking MCP first-tool delegation authorization flow. Evaluates the MCP actor delegation chain and resource audience against the Super Banking MCP Delegation policy in PingOne Authorize before allowing the AI agent to execute MCP tools on behalf of a user. Parameters sent: DecisionContext=McpFirstTool, UserId, ToolName, TokenAudience, ActClientId, NestedActClientId, McpResourceUri, Acr. Policy rules: DENY if TokenAudience does not match McpResourceUri; DENY if ActClientId is not the registered BFF client; DENY if UserId is absent; PERMIT otherwise. After import, configure the Decision Router evaluator (node: mc5eval02b) with branches: condition local.mc6auth01a.payload.output.denied=true routes to Tool Authorization Denied; condition local.mc8func01a.payload.output.stepUpRequired=true routes to Step-Up Required; condition local.mc8func01a.payload.output.hitlRequired=true routes to Human Approval Required; default routes to Tool Authorized.",
